-- Russia's Government Earmarks $5.6 Billion for Technology Hub Near Moscow
-- Lyubov Pronina
-- 2010-07-15T05:10:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/russia-s-government-earmarks-5-6-billion-for-technology-hub-near-moscow.html

          
          
             Russia’s government will set aside
170 billion rubles ($5.6 billion) for the construction of a
technology hub in the Moscow suburb of Skolkovo, President
Dmitry Medvedev said today after meeting with German Chancellor
Angela Merkel.  
 Medvedev invited Germany to invest in “non-strategic”
Russian companies, the leader said after talks in Yekaterinburg
today.  
